Lisa Dodson have been sent this week as part of New America News
Service. Dodson, a fellow at the Radcliffe Public Policy Institute,
teaches at Harvard University on women and poverty. ``Don't Call Us
Out of Name'' is a product of interviews, surveys, observations and
focus groups studying the effects of growing up female in poor
America. A cover shot of the book can be sent to you
electronically. Please contact Aidan McNulty, senior editor, by
