   &UR; The New York Times Syndicate especially recommends this
three-part series, ``To Us, The United States Was the Evil
Empire,'' by Sergei Khrushchev, adapted from American Heritage. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The son of Nikita Khrushchev, he and his wife, Valentina
Golenko, now live in Rhode Island and became U.S. citizens last
year. His book, ``The Creation of a Superpower,'' will be published
by Penn State University Press this fall. Sergei Khrushchev is also
a senior fellow at the Thomas J. Watson Jr. Center for
International Studies at Brown University. &LR;
</P>
