<P>
   __ Part I: ``To Us, the United States Was the Evil Empire'' (In
Russia our lives were spent amid the fear that America, our great
national enemy, would strike a fatal blow if we made the slightest
false step. ... But after living through the horrors of World War
II, we were not frightened by the atomic bomb.) slugged:
BC-EVIL-EMPIRE-WARGAMES-ONE.
</P>
<P>
   __ Part II: ``We Will Bury You'' (We knew the Soviet Union had
no more than half a dozen intercontinental missiles. Despite this
Father used to say, ``We are producing missiles like sausages.'' By
frightening the world with the idea of Soviet missile superiority,
he hoped our side would be construed as equal to the United
States.) slugged: BC-EVIL-EMPIRE-MISSILES-TWO.
</P>
<P>
   __ Part III: ``Father, Castro, Kennedy and The Cuban Missile
Crisis'' (Kennedy was under tremendous pressure. ... Father knew
this, and took it into account when he decided to withdraw the
missiles from Cuba in exchange for Kennedy's promise not to invade
the island _ a promise he trusted. Years before, this would have
been inconceivable: Trust an American president!) slugged:
BC-EVIL-EMPIRE-CUBA-THREE.
