stylishness, waiterwear is expected to make as much of a design
statement as the matchbooks and barstools. It is now possible for
New York diners to confuse their server with a Buddhist priest, a
Benedictine monk, a garage mechanic, a chef, a dishwasher, or a
perfume ad. Anything but a waiter. By Rick Marin.
