<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-18 14:46 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A9168 &Cx1f; tic-z
r a BC-MONTINI-COLUMN-AZR &LR;      01-18 0607
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MONTINI-COLUMN-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CUBAN DAD CAN'T MATCH UNCLE SAM 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By E.J. MONTINI  
   
 c.2000 The Arizona Republic  
 (EDITORS: This article also moving in the ``K'' category)
<TEXT>
<P>
   Them communists in Cuba still don't get it so I figure we have
no choice but to send in the Marines.
</P>
<P>
   That's about the only way we'll convince every cussed madre and
padre on the island to hand over their children so we can ship 'em
north to be raised properly in the land of the free and the home of
the Atlanta Braves. Or, in the case of young Elian Gonzalez, the
Florida Marlins.
</P>
<P>
   As it is, the Marxist muchachos seem to believe a boy is better
off living in the home of his father rather than here, the Home of
the Whopper.
</P>
<P>
   Unfortunately, some bureaucrats in the U.S. government agree
with the reds. They want to ship the 6-year-old back, talking
nonsense about how Elian's father loves him and wants him home.
</P>
<P>
   That's why you and I and every other real live nephew of our
Uncle Sam must let the Cubans know the only people capable of
raising a child are Americans.
</P>
<P>
   Just don't tell 'em about Elizabeth Whittle.
</P>
<P>
   She's an American mother in Phoenix going to jail for 172{ years
for brutalizing her beautiful baby quadruplets. No need to bore the
Bolsheviks with little problems like that.
</P>
<P>
   All we need to do is tell 'em how much better it is for every
child in America than it is for every child in Cuba.
</P>
<P>
   There's no reason to mention Patricia Moreno Oakes, the mother
from Phoenix who turned her 6-year-old daughter into a prostitute
to feed her drug habit.
</P>
<P>
   Also, please, don't bring up the unfortunate story of
6-month-old Denzel Garland, a Phoenix boy who was left in the care
of a teenage cousin only to wind up dead in a dumpster with his
throat slashed.
</P>
<P>
   Those examples are from just one city. Imagine how confusing it
will be if reports from other towns start leaking out? Instead,
simply remind the honchos in Havana about our shopping malls and
video games and Peter Piper Pizzas.
</P>
<P>
   We're under no obligation to tell them about the National Center
for Injury and Prevention Council report showing how unintentional
and intentional firearm injuries are the leading causes of death
for American youngsters.
</P>
<P>
   And we shouldn't cloud the issue with the Hudson Institute study
showing that, among long-term prison inmates, 70 percent grew up
without fathers, including 60 percent of the rapists and 75 percent
of adolescents charged with murder.
</P>
<P>
   Or that fatherless children are three times more likely to fail
in school or commit suicide.
</P>
<P>
   Or that kids living without their dads are 40 times more likely
to suffer child abuse.
</P>
<P>
   We should listen instead to Sen. John McCain, who said of Elian,
``I have had some experience with communist governments, and there
are millions of Americans that have, too. Ask any of them who lived
under it what it was like and whether we should condemn that young
boy to it.''
</P>
<P>
   Can you imagine anything worse than being condemned to live with
your dad?
</P>
<P>
   Still, I imagine the pinkos will try to twist things around by
using McCain's own autobiography, ``Faith of My Fathers.'' They'll
point out that McCain called his dad and granddad the most
important influences in his life.
</P>
<P>
   Remember, they were AMERICAN men. Only U.S. fathers count.
That's what McCain and the others keep trying to explain to Elian
Gonzalez's daddy? You'd figure he would of gotten the message by
now?
</P>
<P>
   What's wrong with them idiot Cubans? Don't they understand
English? &QL; Reach Montini at Ed.Montini(at)ArizonaRepublic.com or
(602) 444-8978. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
