</P>
<P>
   WARSH-COLUMN (Undated) _ It is all very well to seek
accountability for the HMO debacle, but remember that it is the
system itself that is in crisis. By David Warsh.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BKO-JOHNSON (La Crosse, Wis.) _ Dennis Johnson is attempting to
get himself back into professional basketball -- in the unheralded
Continental Basketball Association. By Bob Ryan. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-RAMS (St. Louis) -- No greater example of the differences
between the slick America of 2000 and the more basic world of half
a century ago can be in the differences between the helmets worn by
the Rams and the Bucs. By Michael Madden. 590 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SHAUGHNESSY-COLUMN (Undated) _ Tampa Bay, St. Louis,
Nashville, and Jacksonville. How did Hooterville, Dogpatch, and
Bugtussle miss the cut? By Dan Shaughnessy. 825 words.
</P>
<P>
   SOC-NOTEBOOK (Pasadena, Calif.) -- Revolution coach Fernando
Clavijo has some major decisions to make before pre-season training
begins next week, and among the first will relate to his former
World Cup teammate, John Harkes. By Frank Dell'Apa.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-COLLINS (Melbourne) _ Anna Kournikova and Paradorn
Srichaphan played their parts brilliantly as the Australian Open
cranks into being. By Bud Collins.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-COLUMN (Undated) _ It's already time to nail down entries
for the MassCap and Lou Raffetto is headed for the road. By Ron
Indrisano. 875 words.
