<P>
   COKE-STAHL _ Coca-Cola's board meets today. Directors are
expected to select Jack Stahl as president and chief operating
officer. Watching other developments throughout the day. (Unger,
Atlanta journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   w/COKE-ANALYST _ A well-respected Wall Street analyst predicted
Coca-Cola will be undergoing ``the greatest sea change in its
business in 20 years,'' including cutting as many as 2,000 jobs
from its global workforce. Sanford Bernstein analyst Bill
Pecoriello estimated that about 600 jobs would be eliminated in
Atlanta. ``That's my own analysis, not the company's,'' Pecoriello
said Monday. (Unger, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
