   ECOMMERCE _ For traditional retailers, e-commerce has become a
question of when, not if. Almost all of them agree that the
Internet represents both an opportunity and a necessity. Where
there was panic a year ago after the financialcommunity began
keeping score of online sales, today there is a sense of caution.
Retailers feel they have their very brands, many of which were
carefully built long before the World Wide Web was created, at
stake. The only thing worse than not being on the Internet is doing
