   COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   FBC_ HERITAGE _ The McDonald's Heritage Bowl, viewed as the
Super Bowl of black colleges, is in serious trouble after a
seven-year run at the Georgia Dome. Attendance is sagging and
officials are not sure if the game, which matches teams from the
Southwestern Athletic (SWAC) and Mid-Eastern Athletic (MEAC)
conferences, will be played next year. (Reese, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BASKETBALL/PROS
</P>
<P>
   BKN-HAWKS _ It's a question that seems to arise on a weekly
basis - what's wrong with the Atlanta Hawks? The Hawks ended a
five-day break with a road victory over the Chicago Bulls last
Friday, but returned home to lose consecutive games to Philadelphia
and Milwaukee. How much longer will the Hawks continue in their
slide before drastic changes are made? (Denberg, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
