<HEADLINE>
YOU'VE GOT PICTURES: ELECTRONIC SCRAPBOOKS MADE EASY  
(DW)
</HEADLINE>
   By LONNIE BROWN   
 The Ledger, Lakeland, Fla.   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   More than 85 percent of Americans put their photographs in
albums. That's still easy to do for those who use point-and-shoot
cameras and traditional developing at photo labs.
</P>
<P>
   But photos are more often coming in other forms _ something that
America Online users know since AOL became partners with Kodak to
place a ``You've Got Pictures!'' icon on the AOL welcome screen.
</P>
<P>
   Even if that service is not used, it is possible to scan photos
and send them over the Internet, or to have the roll of film
processed and the pictures turned on photo paper and floppy disk
(or CD-ROM).
</P>
<P>
   American Greetings Scrapbooks &AMP; More (Broderbund; Windows; about
$30) can handle pictures in many ways. It has thousands of
ready-to-print projects, so users can create not only album pages,
but photo cubes and keepsake boxes.
</P>
<P>
   Once pictures are in the electronic album, they can be organized
so pictures are easier to locate in the future.
</P>
<P>
   Pictures can be used to make scrapbooks, pop-up albums, shaped
cards, organizers and photo frames. The program also has hundreds
of captions and sentiments from American Greetings' writers, along
with a large collection of drawings and clip art to use with
projects.
</P>
<P>
   Photo editing tools can resize photos, remove red eye, repair
cracks and scratches in old photos and improve contrast.
</P>
<P>
   STUDY AIDS
</P>
<P>
   The New Millennium Children's Encyclopedia from Simon &AMP; Schuster
links reference works to make a home-reference library:
</P>
<P>
   _ Oxford American Children's Encyclopedia is a computer version
of the nine-volume set.
</P>
<P>
   _ World Book Dictionary for Kids has more than 11,000 entries.
</P>
<P>
   _ World Book Almanac for Kids 1999 has puzzles, pictures, maps,
flags and fascinating facts.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Simon &AMP; Schuster Animal Encyclopedia provides information
about animals around the world.
</P>
<P>
   _ World Book Guide to the World and its Creatures has a fact box
in each country, a timeline listing significant events in the
country's past, and an overview of history, economy, culture and
politics.
</P>
<P>
   The program's Versaware search engine goes through all six works
at once, then provides ``hyperlinks'' like those found on Web pages
to take kids to the material with the click of the mouse. Stars
Future titles can be purchased through an Internet connection and
automatically incorporated into the search engine.
</P>
<P>
   The two CD-ROM set is for Windows-based computers and carries a
street price of about $30.
</P>
<P>
   (Lonnie Brown is associate editor of The Ledger in Lakeland,
Fla., part of the New York Times Regional Newspaper Group. He can
be reached by e-mail at LonnieB001(AT)aol.com.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
