rich and poor keeps widening nine years into a sparkling economic
expansion, New England's six states show some of the country's
widest and narrowest gaps. By Ellen Barry. 850 words.
</P>
<P>
   RAYTHEON-QUARTER (Undated) _ Raytheon Co. may miss earnings
forecasts this year by up to $220 million, the latest in a series
of disappointments for the defense contractor that had promised
improvements. By Ross Kerber. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   AILING-HMO (Boston) _ Salomon Smith Barney begins scouting
options to save Massachusetts' largest HMO from bankruptcy, either
by finding $150 million in cash to resuscitate Harvard Pilgrim
Health Care, or by identifying a buyer for the $2.8 billion-a-year
health plan. By Richard A. Knox and Steven Wilmsen. 800 words.
</P>
