<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, JAN. 19
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-IRAQ-INSPECTIONS-NYT (moved on Monday, Jan. 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Jan. 17,
about the choice of a leader for the new United Nations commission
that is to monitor Iraq's weapons programs misstated the selection
process. Secretary General Kofi Annan named Rolf Ekeus of Sweden
after the Security Council failed to agree on any candidate Annan
was considering. The council was not to make its own nomination.
</P>
<P>
   BC-NORTON-ART-DONATE-NYT (moved on Monday, Jan. 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Jan. 17,
about Peter and Eileen Norton's gift of some 1,000 artworks to 29
institutions omitted a word in the name of one recipient. It is the
Johnson County Community College Gallery of Art in Overland Park,
Kan.
</P>
<P>
   BC-KIDS-BOOKS-AWARDS-NYT (moved on Monday, Jan. 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Jan. 17,
about the American Library Association's annual prizes for
children's literature misspelled the surname of one winner of a
secondary award and the given name of another. The author and
illustrator of ``Sector 7,'' which was named a Caldecott Honor
Book, is David Wiesner, not Weisner. The author of ``My Rows and
Piles of Coins,'' named a King Honor Book for its illustrations by
E.B. Lewis, was written by Tololwa M. Mollel, not Tolowa.
</P>
</TEXT>
